description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit enthusiastic and motivated Healthcare Assistants to join our expanding, Rapid Response team in Derby City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are part or full time with the successful candidates being based at London Road Community Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This role will require you travelling across Derby City and the suburbs, as part of a wider integrated team providing holistic care to patients in their own homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to use your own transport as the geographical patch is large.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It is expected you will have recent experience working in either a health or social care setting. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A good standard of English is required, along with good communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a clinical employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jenna Fraser&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ICTL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jenna.fraser1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
